# Whitelist for `clasp push` (gitignore semantics, clasp 3.x).
#
# Apps Script should contain ONLY:
#   - appsscript.json (manifest)
#   - everything under src/ (.gs and .html partials/pages)
#
# clasp converts any pushed *.js into *.gs, so Node-only scripts under
# scripts/ or assets/ MUST be excluded or they'll execute server-side
# and break the web app (e.g. ReferenceError: require is not defined).

# 1) Block all top-level entries (files + dotfiles + dotdirs)
/*
/.*

# 2) Defensive deep excludes — some ignore matchers walk every path
#    independently and do not propagate a directory exclusion to its
#    contents, so we must spell out the nested junk too.
/.history/**
/.git/**
/.github/**
/.vscode/**
/node_modules/**
/assets/**
# NOTE: /scripts/** intentionally NOT excluded. Both scripts/*.js files
# are typeof-require-guarded so they're harmless no-ops if clasp renames
# them to .gs on push. We deliberately push them to OVERWRITE the broken
# scripts/build-preview.gs that's already on the Apps Script server
# (clasp 3.x's `push -f` only overwrites — it does not delete orphans).
# Once the server is clean you can re-enable /scripts/** here.

# 3) Re-include the manifest + the source tree
!/appsscript.json
!/src
